; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures DAC and generates analog signal out by specific data.
;
; B. Preparation
;    Connecting target port with a suitable instrument.
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. DAC
;    2. PCU/GPIO
;
; D. Default Port
;    1. DAC0    : PA7 (DAO)
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; DAC0
; 1. Config                     : [ 0 p m i c -port 0x1]
;    Operation                  : p (Polling)
;    Mode                       : m (Manual)
;    Reference Level            : i (Internal VDD)
;    Re-load reference          : c (Constant)
;    Output Port (-port)        : 0x01 (Port 1)
;
; PCU (DAC0)
; 1. Port Group                : 0 (PCU Port A)
;
; 2. Port                      : [ 0 7 a 3 ]
;    Pin Number                : 7
;    Pin Mode                  : a (Alternative)
;    Alternative               : 3 (DACO)

; PCU
sendln 'cm pcu'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 0 7 a 3'
mpause 30

; DAC0
sendln 'cm dac'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 0 p m i c -port -0x1'
mpause 30
sendln 'start 0'
